This group is for people who want to keep up-to-date on [url=en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source]open source[/url] software across the web. Here you will recieve notifications on project updates, news, and we pick our own project of the month.

If you wish to edit or add something to the group, you may do so on our [url=https://github.com/ROCKNROLLKID/Open-Source-Community]GitHub page[/url] You may also edit the community logo on our GitHub page, as well. To do so, please go to our GitHub page, then on the right side tab bar, click on "Issues". You may view, edit, and resubmit the community logo there.

You may view the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/groups/opencommunity/discussions/0/523897653295885376]List of open-source software[/url] that we support in the discussion thread of this group.

To see a list of open-source websites, such as search engines, email services, and hosting services, please view our [url=https://steamcommunity.com/groups/opencommunity/discussions/0/358415103479084969]List of websites[/url] thread.

To see a list of open-source hardware, which can be anything from computers to house hold appliances, please view our [url=http://steamcommunity.com/groups/opencommunity/discussions/0/154643085273052654/]List of Hardware[/url] section.

As a alternative, you may also view a list of [url=https://steamcommunity.com/groups/opencommunity/discussions/0/412446890553037315]Open-source licenses[/url] that you may use if you wish to build your own open-source program.

Any and all credit to anyone who has helped our community is posted on our [url=https://steamcommunity.com/groups/opencommunity/discussions/0/598199244886622774]List of contributors[/url] page. You may also find the staff list there, as well.

If you wish to join the staff team or do volunteer work for us, you may view the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/groups/opencommunity/discussions/0/496879865898736175]Job board\Volunteer work[/url] page.

If you want to make a nomination request for project of the month, or have any comments or suggestions for project of the month, please make a discussion thread at our [url=https://steamcommunity.com/groups/opencommunity/discussions/4]Project of the month[/url] forums.

If you have any software, website, or hardware suggestions, feel free to post about it. Please keep it open-source only.
